h4.page-header Install Apple Xcode Command Line Tools
p
  strong Instruction
ol
  li Install the command line tools by entering the following command into your terminal.
  pre xcode-select --install
  li Restart your computer.
  li Verify that the installation was successful.
  pre xcode-select -p
  li Typing the above should return the following:
  pre
    | /Library/Developer/CommandLineTools
p
  strong Reason
p
  | Installation of many common Unix-based tools requires a GCC compiler. The Xcode Command Line Tools include a GCC compiler.

h4.page-header Install Homebrew
p
  strong Instruction
ol
  li To install run this command in terminal.
  pre ruby -e "$(curl -fsSL https://raw.github.com/Homebrew/install/master/install)"
  li Verify installation was successful.
  pre brew doctor
  li You should see:
  pre Your system is ready to brew
p
  strong Reason
p Homebrew is a package management system that simplifies the installation of software.

