h4.page-header Set Sublime as default editor
p
  strong Instruction
ol
  li Be sure that sublime is in your Applications folder.
  li Open bash profile.
  pre open ~/.bash_profile
  li Place alias within bash profile.
  pre alias subl="/Applications/Sublime\ Text.app/Contents/SharedSupport/bin/subl"
  li Reload bash profile to save the changes.
  pre source ~/.bash_profile
  li Test that it worked.
  pre subl .
p
  strong Reason
p
  | We will be constantly using Sublime editor for all of our code. This is a handy alias that easily opens up sublime for us.

h4.page-header Install rbenv
p
  strong Instruction
ol
  li Download rbenv via brew
  pre brew install rbenv
  pre rbenv init
  li Install the latest version of ruby
  pre rbenv install 2.2.3
p
  strong Reason
p Have stable ruby version to develop on.
